One fix for this was to put ``static_cast<func_decl*>()`` around the ``func_decl_ref`` arguments you were passing to ``mk_app()`` however that didn't seem very elegant and I also wasn't sure if doing that screw up any reference counting mechanism you have. So I have left this for now.

When calling a SimProcedure the following problems occur:
- return edges are added to the PLT-node instead of the simprocedure
- an extra UnResolvableTarget node is added to the PLT nodes.

I've created a very simple example:
```
int main () { f(); }

int f () {
  FILE * file = fopen("binary", "rb");
  fclose (file);
  return 0;
}
```
